description:
&lt;p&gt;The Durham and Darlington Adult Community Mental Health Teams are planning to restructure the way services operate and as such an opportunity has arisen for a Band 3 HCA to join the Darlington Community Teams. The role predominantly is to deliver Physical Health &amp; Clozapine monitoring Interventions, however there will be an expectation to work within and support the wider community teams with some one to one and group work with Service Users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires a minimum of current training in Physical Health Checks, Venepuncture, ECG and Lifestyle Factors, however candidates with relevant experience in the health service would be considered and training would be provided. Experience in clozapine monitoring would be an advantage but training in this area would also be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have completed the Diploma in Health and Social Care Level 3 or equivalent. Candidates must also have Literacy and Numeracy level 2 or equivalent and must complete the Trust Healthcare Assistant competencies within their probationary period (first 6 months in role).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Brennan, Team Manger fiona.brennan1@nhs.net 07825 850835 or 01325 552322&lt;/p&gt;
